{"title_page": "Sankt Veit in der S\u00fcdsteiermark", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n| name            = Sankt Veit in der S\u00fcdsteiermark\n| native_name     = \n| settlement_type = \n<!-- Images     -->\n| image_skyline   = \n| imagesize       = \n| image_caption   = \n| image_shield    = \n| shield_size     = \n| shield_link     = \n<!-- Maps           -->\n| pushpin_map         = Austria\n| pushpin_mapsize     = 270\n| pushpin_map_caption = Location within Austria\n| image_map           = \n| mapsize             = \n| map_alt             =\n| map_caption         = Location within Murtal district\n<!-- Location    -->\n| coordinates       = {{coord|46|44|52|N|15|37|36|E|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type  = Country\n| subdivision_name  = [[Austria]]\n| subdivision_type1 = [[States of Austria|State]]\n| subdivision_name1 = [[Styria]]\n| subdivision_type2 = [[District (Austria)|District]]\n| subdivision_name2 = [[Murtal District|Murtal]]\n| parts_type        = \n| parts_style       = para\n| p1                = \n<!-- Leaders -->\n| leader_title  = [[Burgomaster|Mayor]]\n| leader_name   = Manfred Tatzl\n| leader_party  = {{Polparty|Austria| \u00d6VP }}\n| leader_title1 = \n| leader_name1  = \n<!-- Statistics -->\n| area_footnotes   = {{Austria population Wikidata|area_footnotes}}\n| area_total_km2   = {{Austria population Wikidata|area_total_km2}}\n| area_metro_km2   = \n| elevation_m      = 260\n| elevation_max_m  = \n| elevation_min_m  = \n| population_as_of = {{Austria population Wikidata|population_as_of}}\n| population_footnotes = {{Austria population Wikidata|population_footnotes}}\n| population_total = {{Austria population Wikidata|population_total}}\n| population_urban =  \n| population_metro =  \n| population_note  = \n| population_density_km2 = auto\n| established_title = \n| established_date  = \n| timezone          = [[Central European Time|CET]]\n| timezone_DST      = [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]]\n| utc_offset        = +1\n| utc_offset_DST    = +2\n| registration_plate = \n| postal_code_type   = [[List of postal codes in Austria|Postal code]]\n| postal_code        = 8423, 8421, 8422, 8435, 8481\n| area_code_type = [[Telephone numbers in Austria|Area code]]\n| area_code      = 03453\n| website   = [http://www.st-veit-suedsteiermark.gv.at/ www.st-veit-suedsteiermark.gv.at]\n| footnotes = \n}}\n[[Image:Pfarrkirche Sankt Veit am Vogau 02.jpg |thumb|The namesake Catholic Pfarrkirche church, Hl. Veit.]]\n\n'''Sankt Veit in der S\u00fcdsteiermark''' is a municipality since 2015 in the [[Leibnitz District]] of [[Styria]], Austria. The population was 4,069 residents (as of 1 January 2016).\n\nThe municipality, Sankt Veit in der S\u00fcdsteiermark, was created as part of the [[Steierm\u00e4rkische Gemeindestrukturreform|Styria municipal structural reform]],<ref>[http://www.gemeindestrukturreform.steiermark.at/cms/beitrag/11558627/69294537 Steierm\u00e4rkische Gemeindestrukturreform]</ref>\nat the end of 2014, by merging the former towns [[Sankt Veit am Vogau]] and [[Sankt Nikolai ob Dra\u00dfling]], both in the political district Leibnitz, plus the town [[Weinburg am Sa\u00dfbach]] in the political [[S\u00fcdoststeiermark District]].<ref>[https://www.ris.bka.gv.at/Dokumente/LgblAuth/LGBLA_ST_20140626_72/LGBLA_ST_20140626_72.pdfsig Kundmachung der Steierm\u00e4rkischen Landesregierung] of 28 November 2013, about the union of market town Sankt Veit am Vogau and the municipality Sankt Nikolai ob Dra\u00dfling, both in Leibnitz District, and the town Weinburg am Sa\u00dfbach, in political district S\u00fcdoststeiermark. ''Landesgesetzblatt f\u00fcr die Steiermark''. 26 June 2014. Nr. 72, Jahrgang 2014. {{ZDB-ID|705127-x}}. p. 1.</ref>\n\nThe borders of the S\u00fcdoststeiermark District and Leibnitz District were shifted, so that the new municipality would lie completely within Leibnitz District.<ref>[https://www.ris.bka.gv.at/Dokumente/LgblAuth/LGBLA_ST_20140910_99/LGBLA_ST_20140910_99.pdfsig Verordnung der Steierm\u00e4rkischen Landesregierung] vom 10. Juli 2014, mit der die Steierm\u00e4rkische Bezirkshauptmannschaftenverordnung ge\u00e4ndert wird. ''Landesgesetzblatt f\u00fcr die Steiermark''. 10 September 2014. Nr. 99 Jahrgang 2014. {{ZDB-ID|705127-x}}.</ref>\n\nThe former municipality [[Weinburg am Sa\u00dfbach]] was until the end of 2012 in [[Radkersburg District]] and had the Kfz-code \"RA\u201c. From the middle of 2013 until the end of 2014, the code had abbreviation \"SO\"; in 2015 it was set as \"LB\".\n\n== Geography ==\n\n=== Municipality arrangement ===\nThe municipality territory includes the following 11 [[Katastralgemeinde]]n and 16 sections (populations as of 1 January 2015<ref>[http://www.statistik.at/wcm/idc/idcplg?IdcService=GET_NATIVE_FILE&RevisionSelectionMethod=LatestReleased&dDocName=103419 Einwohner nach Ortschaften] (Excel-Datei, 766 KB); accessed 29 July 2015</ref>):\n;Katastralgemeinden\n{{colbegin}}\n* H\u00fctt {{ns}} ({{cvt|592.49|ha |disp=or}})\n* Labuttendorf (478.95 ha)\n* Lind {{ns}} ({{cvt|342.25|ha |disp=or}})\n* Lipsch (333.30 ha)\n* Neutersdorf (353.21 ha)\n* Perbersdorf bei St. Veit (413.10 ha)\n* Pichla (698.92 ha)\n* St. Nikolai ob Dra\u00dfling (1,174.97 ha)\n* St. Veit am Vogau (1,015.12 ha)\n* Siebing &nbsp; ({{cvt|525.90|ha |disp=or}})\n* Weinburg ({{cvt|936.87|ha |disp=or}})\n{{colend}}\n;Ortschaften\n{{colbegin}}\n* [[H\u00fctt (Gemeinde St. Veit in der S\u00fcdsteiermark)|H\u00fctt]] (185)\n* [[Labuttendorf]] (173)\n* [[Leitersdorf (Gemeinde St. Veit in der S\u00fcdsteiermark)|Leitersdorf]] (135)\n* [[Lind bei St. Veit am Vogau]] (220)\n* [[Lipsch (Gemeinde St. Veit in der S\u00fcdsteiermark)|Lipsch]] (182)\n* [[Marchtring]] (19)\n* [[Neutersdorf]] (92)\n* [[Perbersdorf bei Sankt Veit]] (146)\n* [[Pichla bei Mureck]] (156)\n* [[Priebing]] (101)\n* [[Rabenhof (Gemeinde St. Veit in der S\u00fcdsteiermark)|Rabenhof]] (149)\n* [[Sankt Nikolai ob Dra\u00dfling]] (771)\n* [[Sankt Veit am Vogau]] (598)\n* [[Siebing (Gemeinde St. Veit in der S\u00fcdsteiermark)|Siebing]] (272)\n* [[Wagendorf (Gemeinde St. Veit in der S\u00fcdsteiermark)|Wagendorf]] (515)\n* [[Weinburg am Sa\u00dfbach]] (363)\n{{colend}}\n\n=== Neighboring municipalities ===\nThe municipality is bordered by seven neighboring towns, four were in [[S\u00fcdoststeiermark District]]&nbsp;(SO).\n{{adjacent communities|noicon=yes|width=auto\n|title =  \n|Northwest = \n|North = [[Schwarzautal]]\n|Northeast = [[Mettersdorf am Sa\u00dfbach]] (SO)<br />and<br />[[Sankt Peter am Ottersbach]] (SO)\n|West = [[Gabersdorf (Steiermark)|Gabersdorf]]\n|Center = [[File:Compass_rose_simple.svg|80px|Neighbouring communities]]\n|East = [[Mureck]] (SO)\n|Southwest = \n|South = [[Stra\u00df in Steiermark]]\n|Southeast = [[Murfeld]] (SO)\n}}\n\n== Demographics ==\n<timeline>\nColors=\n id:lightgrey value:gray(0.9)\n id:darkgrey  value:gray(0.7)\n id:sfondo value:rgb(1,1,1)\n\nImageSize  = width:550 height:auto barincrement:28\nPlotArea   = left:40 bottom:40 top:20 right:20\nDateFormat = x.y\nPeriod     = from:0 till:4300\nTimeAxis   = orientation:horizontal\nAlignBars  = late\nScaleMajor = gridcolor:darkgrey  increment:500 start:0\nScaleMinor = gridcolor:lightgrey increment:125 start:0\nBackgroundColors = canvas:sfondo\n\nPlotData=\n  color:skyblue width:20 shift:(-50,-5) fontsize:M anchor:till\n bar:1869 from:0 till:4027 text:4.027\n bar:1880 from:0 till:4253 text:4.253\n bar:1890 from:0 till:4218 text:4.218\n bar:1900 from:0 till:4092 text:4.092\n bar:1910 from:0 till:4239 text:4.239\n bar:1923 from:0 till:4091 text:4.091\n bar:1934 from:0 till:4164 text:4.164\n bar:1939 from:0 till:4030 text:4.030\n bar:1951 from:0 till:4002 text:4.002\n bar:1961 from:0 till:3635 text:3.635\n bar:1971 from:0 till:3768 text:3.768\n bar:1981 from:0 till:3907 text:3.907\n bar:1991 from:0 till:4004 text:4.004\n bar:2001 from:0 till:4113 text:4.113\n bar:2011 from:0 till:4013 text:4.013\n bar:2016 from:0 till:4069 text:4.069\n\nTextData=\n fontsize:M pos:(35,20)\n text:\"Quelle: Statistik Austria, alle Daten laut Gebietsstand 2016\"\n</timeline>\n\n[[Image:Orgel St Veit am Vogau.JPG |thumb |[[Johann Ignaz Egedacher|Egedacher]]-Orgel der Veitskirche]]\n[[Image:Pfarrhof St Veit am Vogau 3.JPG |thumb|Pfarrhof in St. Veit am Vogau]]\n[[Image: Schloss weinburg am sassbach.JPG |thumb|Schloss Weinburg am Sa\u00dfbach]]\n\n== Politics ==\n\n=== Mayor ===\nManfred Tatzl (\u00d6VP) was elected mayor of the newly formed municipality on 20 April 2015, in the inaugural meeting of the Municipal Council.<ref name=\"GemVst\">Gemeinde St. Veit in der S\u00fcdsteiermark: [http://www.st-veit-suedsteiermark.gv.at/fileadmin/user_upload/documents/Gemeinde/Gemeinde/Rundschreiben/2015_03_Gemeinderundschreiben.pdf ''Gemeindenachrichten Juni 2015''] (pdf-Dokument, 367 KB), abgerufen am 15. Juni 2015</ref> Tatzl was already, at the end of 2014, the mayor of the former municipality of St. Veit am Vogau and led from January 1, 2015, the transactions of the merged municipality as government commissioner.\n\nJosef Pratter, the nearly 25-year mayor of St. Nikolai ob Dra\u00dfling, was and the former mayor of the municipality of Weinburg am Sa\u00dfbach, Susanne Lucchesi-Palli, came to the election.<ref>Gemeinden St. Nikolai ob Dra\u00dfling, Weinburg am Sa\u00dfbach und St. Veit am Vogau: [http://www.st-veit-suedsteiermark.gv.at/fileadmin/user_upload/documents/Gemeinde/Gemeinde/Gemeindezeitung/gemeinsam_geschafft_2014_03_web.pdf ''Gemeinsam Geschafft \u2013 Amtliche Informationszeitung der Gemeinden St. Nikolai ob Dra\u00dfling, Weinburg am Sa\u00dfbach und St. Veit am Vogau, 4.&nbsp;Ausgabe 4/2014''] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150701141658/http://www.st-veit-suedsteiermark.gv.at/fileadmin/user_upload/documents/Gemeinde/Gemeinde/Gemeindezeitung/gemeinsam_geschafft_2014_03_web.pdf |date=2015-07-01 }} (pdf-Dokument, 4,02&nbsp;MB), abgerufen am 15.&nbsp;Juni 2015</ref>\n\nWith the results from April 30, 2015, Manfred Tatzl traveled by his council mandate, because he wants to conduct the business of the merged municipality as a \"People's Mayor\". [7]\n\nThe town council also includes the first deputy mayor Gerhard Rohrer, the second Deputy Mayor Harald Sch\u00f6gler, the municipality treasurer Georg Pock and board member Rudolf Reinprecht.<ref name=\"GemVst\" /><ref name=\"GdeNachr_3/2015\" />\n\n=== Municipality council ===\nThe town council has 21 members. After the 2015 election, the council had the following results:<ref name=\"GdeNachr_3/2015\">Gemeinde St. Veit in der S\u00fcdsteiermark: [http://www.st-veit-suedsteiermark.gv.at/fileadmin/user_upload/documents/Gemeinde/Gemeinde/Rundschreiben/2015_02_Gemeinderundschreiben.pdf ''Gemeindenachrichten M\u00e4rz 2015''] (pdf-Dokument, 500 KB), abgerufen am 15. Juni 2015</ref>\n* 12 Mandate [[\u00d6VP]]\n* {{0}}6 Mandate [[SP\u00d6]]\n* {{0}}3 Mandate [[FP\u00d6]]\n\nThe prior elections brought the following results:\n{| class=\"wikitable zebra\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ \n|- class=\"hintergrundfarbe9\"\n! rowspan=\"3\" | Party\n! colspan=\"3\" | 2015\n! colspan=\"9\" | 2010\n|- class=\"hintergrundfarbe9\"\n! colspan=\"3\" | St. Veit in der<br />S\u00fcdsteiermark !! colspan=\"3\" | St. Veit<br />am Vogau !! colspan=\"3\" | St. Nikolai<br />ob Dra\u00dfling !! colspan=\"3\" | Weinburg<br />am Sa\u00dfbach\n|- class=\"hintergrundfarbe9\"\n! Votes !! % !! Mandate\n! St. !! % !! M.\n! St. !! % !! M.\n! St. !! % !! M.\n|- \n| style=\"text-align:left\" | [[\u00d6VP]]\n| 1458 || 56 || 12\n| 767 || 58 || 9\n| 588 || 74 || 11\n| 497 || 69 || 10\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | [[SP\u00d6]]\n| {{0}}| 736 || 28 || {{0}}6\n| 518 || 39 || 6\n| 107 || 13 || {{0}}2\n| colspan=\"3\" | ''not running''\n|- \n| style=\"text-align:left\" | [[FP\u00d6]]\n| {{0}}421 || 16 || {{0}}3\n| {{0}}43 || {{0}}3 || 0\n| {{0}}99 || 12 || {{0}}2\n| colspan=\"3\" | ''not running''\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | Einigkeit lohnt sich\n| colspan=\"3\" | ''not running''\n| colspan=\"3\" | ''not running''\n| colspan=\"3\" | ''not running''\n| 228 || 31 || {{0}}5\n|- class=\"hintergrundfarbe9\"\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |  Counts\n! colspan=\"3\" | 3.444\n! colspan=\"3\" | 1.530\n! colspan=\"3\" | 927\n! colspan=\"3\" | 912\n|- class=\"hintergrundfarbe9\"\n! style=\"text-align:left\" | Percentage\n! colspan=\"3\" | 77%\n! colspan=\"3\" | 87%\n! colspan=\"3\" | 87%\n! colspan=\"3\" | 83%\n|}\n\n=== Coat of arms ===\n<gallery mode=\"nolines\" caption=\"Wappen der Vorg\u00e4ngergemeinden\" widths=\"90px\" style=\"float:right\">\nAUT Sankt Veit am Vogau COA.jpg|Sankt Veit am Vogau\nAUT Sankt Nikolai ob Dra\u00dfling COA.jpg|Sankt Nikolai ob Dra\u00dfling\nAUT Weinburg am Sa\u00dfbach COA.jpg|Weinburg am Sa\u00dfbach\n</gallery>\n\nAll three predecessors had a town crest. Because of the merger, the crests lost their official validity on January 1, 2015. The authorization of the municipal coat of arms for the joined community took effect on 25 October 2016.<ref>[https://www.ris.bka.gv.at/Dokumente/LgblAuth/LGBLA_ST_20161017_124/LGBLA_ST_20161017_124.html 124. Verlautbarung der Steierm\u00e4rkischen Landesregierung vom 13. Oktober 2016 \u00fcber die Verleihung des Rechtes zur F\u00fchrung eines Gemeindewappens an die Marktgemeinde Sankt Veit in der S\u00fcdsteiermark (politischer Bezirk Leibnitz)], abgerufen am 28. Oktober 2016</ref><br>\n[[Blazon]] (crest description):\n: \"Above the silvery shield-foot, over a black, silver-floated wave-beam green three grapes growing from common origin upward and two flat wine leaves, in blue a golden, richly arranged and of window and door fifteenfold black perforated with volute gable and two with Knauf and cross at golden towers; between these, a silver lion's head\".\n<!--\n: \u201e\u00dcber silbernem Schildfu\u00df, darin \u00fcber schwarzem, silbern geflutetem Wellenbalken gr\u00fcn drei aus gemeinsamem Ursprung nach oben wachsende Weintrauben und zwei ebensolche Weinbl\u00e4tter, in Blau eine goldene, reich gegliederte und von Fenstern und T\u00fcr f\u00fcnfzehnfach schwarz durchbrochene Kirchenfassade mit Volutengiebel samt zwei mit Knauf und Kreuz besteckten goldenen Zwiebelt\u00fcrmen, zwischen diesen ein silbernes L\u00f6wenhaupt.\u201c -->\n\n== Culture and sights ==\n\n{{Empty section|date=November 2016}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category}}\n{{StatistikAustria|61056}}\n* Town of St. Veit in der Sudsteiermark: [http://www.st-veit-suedsteiermark.gv.at/ ''Official Homepage''] (in German)\n\n{{Leibnitz}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sankt Veit in der Sudsteiermark}}\n[[Category:Cities and towns in Leibnitz District]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n| name            = Sankt Veit in der S\u00fcdsteiermark\n| native_name     = \n| settlement_type = \n<!-- Images     -->\n| image_skyline   = \n| imagesize       = \n| image_caption   = \n| image_shield    = \n| shield_size     = \n| shield_link     = \n<!-- Maps           -->\n| pushpin_map         = Austria\n| pushpin_mapsize     = 270\n| pushpin_map_caption = Location within Austria\n| image_map           = \n| mapsize             = \n| map_alt             =\n| map_caption         = Location within Murtal district\n<!-- Location    -->\n| coordinates       = {{coord|46|44|52|N|15|37|36|E|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type  = Country\n| subdivision_name  = [[Austria]]\n| subdivision_type1 = [[States of Austria|State]]\n| subdivision_name1 = [[Styria]]\n| subdivision_type2 = [[District (Austria)|District]]\n| subdivision_name2 = [[Murtal District|Murtal]]\n| parts_type        = \n| parts_style       = para\n| p1                = \n<!-- Leaders -->\n| leader_title  = [[Burgomaster|Mayor]]\n| leader_name   = Manfred Tatzl\n| leader_party  = {{Polparty|Austria| \u00d6VP }}\n| leader_title1 = \n| leader_name1  = \n<!-- Statistics -->\n| area_footnotes   = {{Austria population Wikidata|area_footnotes}}\n| area_total_km2   = {{Austria population Wikidata|area_total_km2}}\n| area_metro_km2   = \n| elevation_m      = 260\n| elevation_max_m  = \n| elevation_min_m  = \n| population_as_of = {{Austria population Wikidata|population_as_of}}\n| population_footnotes = {{Austria population Wikidata|population_footnotes}}\n| population_total = {{Austria population Wikidata|population_total}}\n| population_urban =  \n| population_metro =  \n| population_note  = \n| population_density_km2 = auto\n| established_title = \n| established_date  = \n| timezone          = [[Central European Time|CET]]\n| timezone_DST      = [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]]\n| utc_offset        = +1\n| utc_offset_DST    = +2\n| registration_plate = \n| postal_code_type   = [[List of postal codes in Austria|Postal code]]\n| postal_code        = 8423, 8421, 8422, 8435, 8481\n| area_code_type = [[Telephone numbers in Austria|Area code]]\n| area_code      = 03453\n| website   = [http://www.st-veit-suedsteiermark.gv.at/ www.st-veit-suedsteiermark.gv.at]\n| footnotes = \n}}\n[[Image:Pfarrkirche Sankt Veit am Vogau 02.jpg |thumb|The namesake Catholic Pfarrkirche church, Hl. Veit.]]\n\n'''Sankt Veit in der S\u00fcdsteiermark''' is a municipality since 2015 in the [[Leibnitz District]] of [[Styria]], Austria. The population was 4,069 residents (as of 1 January 2016).\n\nThe municipality, Sankt Veit in der S\u00fcdsteiermark, was created as part of the [[Steierm\u00e4rkische Gemeindestrukturreform|Styria municipal structural reform]],<ref>[http://www.gemeindestrukturreform.steiermark.at/cms/beitrag/11558627/69294537 Steierm\u00e4rkische Gemeindestrukturreform]</ref>\nat the end of 2014, by merging the former towns [[Sankt Veit am Vogau]] and [[Sankt Nikolai ob Dra\u00dfling]], both in the political district Leibnitz, plus the town [[Weinburg am Sa\u00dfbach]] in the political [[S\u00fcdoststeiermark District]].<ref>[https://www.ris.bka.gv.at/Dokumente/LgblAuth/LGBLA_ST_20140626_72/LGBLA_ST_20140626_72.pdfsig Kundmachung der Steierm\u00e4rkischen Landesregierung] of 28 November 2013, about the union of market town Sankt Veit am Vogau and the municipality Sankt Nikolai ob Dra\u00dfling, both in Leibnitz District, and the town Weinburg am Sa\u00dfbach, in political district S\u00fcdoststeiermark. ''Landesgesetzblatt f\u00fcr die Steiermark''. 26 June 2014. Nr. 72, Jahrgang 2014. {{ZDB-ID|705127-x}}. p. 1.</ref>\n\nThe borders of the S\u00fcdoststeiermark District and Leibnitz District were shifted, so that the new municipality would lie completely within Leibnitz District.<ref>[https://www.ris.bka.gv.at/Dokumente/LgblAuth/LGBLA_ST_20140910_99/LGBLA_ST_20140910_99.pdfsig Verordnung der Steierm\u00e4rkischen Landesregierung] vom 10. Juli 2014, mit der die Steierm\u00e4rkische Bezirkshauptmannschaftenverordnung ge\u00e4ndert wird. ''Landesgesetzblatt f\u00fcr die Steiermark''. 10 September 2014. Nr. 99 Jahrgang 2014. {{ZDB-ID|705127-x}}.</ref>\n\nThe former municipality [[Weinburg am Sa\u00dfbach]] was until the end of 2012 in [[Radkersburg District]] and had the Kfz-code \"RA\u201c. From the middle of 2013 until the end of 2014, the code had abbreviation \"SO\"; in 2015 it was set as \"LB\".\n\n== Geography ==\n\n=== Municipality arrangement ===\nThe municipality territory includes the following 11 [[Katastralgemeinde]]n and 16 sections (populations as of 1 January 2015<ref>[http://www.statistik.at/wcm/idc/idcplg?IdcService=GET_NATIVE_FILE&RevisionSelectionMethod=LatestReleased&dDocName=103419 Einwohner nach Ortschaften] (Excel-Datei, 766 KB); accessed 29 July 2015</ref>):\n;Katastralgemeinden\n{{colbegin}}\n* H\u00fctt {{ns}} ({{cvt|592.49|ha |disp=or}})\n* Labuttendorf (478.95 ha)\n* Lind {{ns}} ({{cvt|342.25|ha |disp=or}})\n* Lipsch (333.30 ha)\n* Neutersdorf (353.21 ha)\n* Perbersdorf bei St. Veit (413.10 ha)\n* Pichla (698.92 ha)\n* St. Nikolai ob Dra\u00dfling (1,174.97 ha)\n* St. Veit am Vogau (1,015.12 ha)\n* Siebing &nbsp; ({{cvt|525.90|ha |disp=or}})\n* Weinburg ({{cvt|936.87|ha |disp=or}})\n{{colend}}\n;Ortschaften\n{{colbegin}}\n* [[H\u00fctt (Gemeinde St. Veit in der S\u00fcdsteiermark)|H\u00fctt]] (185)\n* [[Labuttendorf]] (173)\n* [[Leitersdorf (Gemeinde St. Veit in der S\u00fcdsteiermark)|Leitersdorf]] (135)\n* [[Lind bei St. Veit am Vogau]] (220)\n* [[Lipsch (Gemeinde St. Veit in der S\u00fcdsteiermark)|Lipsch]] (182)\n* [[Marchtring]] (19)\n* [[Neutersdorf]] (92)\n* [[Perbersdorf bei Sankt Veit]] (146)\n* [[Pichla bei Mureck]] (156)\n* [[Priebing]] (101)\n* [[Rabenhof (Gemeinde St. Veit in der S\u00fcdsteiermark)|Rabenhof]] (149)\n* [[Sankt Nikolai ob Dra\u00dfling]] (771)\n* [[Sankt Veit am Vogau]] (598)\n* [[Siebing (Gemeinde St. Veit in der S\u00fcdsteiermark)|Siebing]] (272)\n* [[Wagendorf (Gemeinde St. Veit in der S\u00fcdsteiermark)|Wagendorf]] (515)\n* [[Weinburg am Sa\u00dfbach]] (363)\n{{colend}}\n\n=== Neighboring municipalities ===\nThe municipality is bordered by seven neighboring towns, four were in [[S\u00fcdoststeiermark District]]&nbsp;(SO).\n{{adjacent communities|noicon=yes|width=auto\n|title =  \n|Northwest = \n|North = [[Schwarzautal]]\n|Northeast = [[Mettersdorf am Sa\u00dfbach]] (SO)<br />and<br />[[Sankt Peter am Ottersbach]] (SO)\n|West = [[Gabersdorf (Steiermark)|Gabersdorf]]\n|Center = [[File:Compass_rose_simple.svg|80px|Neighbouring communities]]\n|East = [[Mureck]] (SO)\n|Southwest = \n|South = [[Stra\u00df in Steiermark]]\n|Southeast = [[Murfeld]] (SO)\n}}\n\n== Demographics ==\n<timeline>\nColors=\n id:lightgrey value:gray(0.9)\n id:darkgrey  value:gray(0.7)\n id:sfondo value:rgb(1,1,1)\n\nImageSize  = width:550 height:auto barincrement:28\nPlotArea   = left:40 bottom:40 top:20 right:20\nDateFormat = x.y\nPeriod     = from:0 till:4300\nTimeAxis   = orientation:horizontal\nAlignBars  = late\nScaleMajor = gridcolor:darkgrey  increment:500 start:0\nScaleMinor = gridcolor:lightgrey increment:125 start:0\nBackgroundColors = canvas:sfondo\n\nPlotData=\n  color:skyblue width:20 shift:(-50,-5) fontsize:M anchor:till\n bar:1869 from:0 till:4027 text:4.027\n bar:1880 from:0 till:4253 text:4.253\n bar:1890 from:0 till:4218 text:4.218\n bar:1900 from:0 till:4092 text:4.092\n bar:1910 from:0 till:4239 text:4.239\n bar:1923 from:0 till:4091 text:4.091\n bar:1934 from:0 till:4164 text:4.164\n bar:1939 from:0 till:4030 text:4.030\n bar:1951 from:0 till:4002 text:4.002\n bar:1961 from:0 till:3635 text:3.635\n bar:1971 from:0 till:3768 text:3.768\n bar:1981 from:0 till:3907 text:3.907\n bar:1991 from:0 till:4004 text:4.004\n bar:2001 from:0 till:4113 text:4.113\n bar:2011 from:0 till:4013 text:4.013\n bar:2016 from:0 till:4069 text:4.069\n\nTextData=\n fontsize:M pos:(35,20)\n text:\"Quelle: Statistik Austria, alle Daten laut Gebietsstand 2016\"\n</timeline>\n\n[[Image:Orgel St Veit am Vogau.JPG |thumb |[[Johann Ignaz Egedacher|Egedacher]]-Orgel der Veitskirche]]\n[[Image:Pfarrhof St Veit am Vogau 3.JPG |thumb|Pfarrhof in St. Veit am Vogau]]\n[[Image: Schloss weinburg am sassbach.JPG |thumb|Schloss Weinburg am Sa\u00dfbach]]\n\n== Politics ==\n\n=== Mayor ===\nManfred Tatzl (\u00d6VP) was elected mayor of the newly formed municipality on 20 April 2015, in the inaugural meeting of the Municipal Council.<ref name=\"GemVst\">Gemeinde St. Veit in der S\u00fcdsteiermark: [http://www.st-veit-suedsteiermark.gv.at/fileadmin/user_upload/documents/Gemeinde/Gemeinde/Rundschreiben/2015_03_Gemeinderundschreiben.pdf ''Gemeindenachrichten Juni 2015''] (pdf-Dokument, 367 KB), abgerufen am 15. Juni 2015</ref> Tatzl was already, at the end of 2014, the mayor of the former municipality of St. Veit am Vogau and led from January 1, 2015, the transactions of the merged municipality as government commissioner.\n\nJosef Pratter, the nearly 25-year mayor of St. Nikolai ob Dra\u00dfling, was and the former mayor of the municipality of Weinburg am Sa\u00dfbach, Susanne Lucchesi-Palli, came to the election.<ref>Gemeinden St. Nikolai ob Dra\u00dfling, Weinburg am Sa\u00dfbach und St. Veit am Vogau: [http://www.st-veit-suedsteiermark.gv.at/fileadmin/user_upload/documents/Gemeinde/Gemeinde/Gemeindezeitung/gemeinsam_geschafft_2014_03_web.pdf ''Gemeinsam Geschafft \u2013 Amtliche Informationszeitung der Gemeinden St. Nikolai ob Dra\u00dfling, Weinburg am Sa\u00dfbach und St. Veit am Vogau, 4.&nbsp;Ausgabe 4/2014''] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150701141658/http://www.st-veit-suedsteiermark.gv.at/fileadmin/user_upload/documents/Gemeinde/Gemeinde/Gemeindezeitung/gemeinsam_geschafft_2014_03_web.pdf |date=2015-07-01 }} (pdf-Dokument, 4,02&nbsp;MB), abgerufen am 15.&nbsp;Juni 2015</ref>\n\nWith the results from April 30, 2015, Manfred Tatzl traveled by his council mandate, because he wants to conduct the business of the merged municipality as a \"People's Mayor\". [7]\n\nThe town council also includes the first deputy mayor Gerhard Rohrer, the second Deputy Mayor Harald Sch\u00f6gler, the municipality treasurer Georg Pock and board member Rudolf Reinprecht.<ref name=\"GemVst\" /><ref name=\"GdeNachr_3/2015\" />\n\n=== Municipality council ===\nThe town council has 21 members. After the 2015 election, the council had the following results:<ref name=\"GdeNachr_3/2015\">Gemeinde St. Veit in der S\u00fcdsteiermark: [http://www.st-veit-suedsteiermark.gv.at/fileadmin/user_upload/documents/Gemeinde/Gemeinde/Rundschreiben/2015_02_Gemeinderundschreiben.pdf ''Gemeindenachrichten M\u00e4rz 2015''] (pdf-Dokument, 500 KB), abgerufen am 15. Juni 2015</ref>\n* 12 Mandate [[\u00d6VP]]\n* {{0}}6 Mandate [[SP\u00d6]]\n* {{0}}3 Mandate [[FP\u00d6]]\n\nThe prior elections brought the following results:\n{| class=\"wikitable zebra\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ \n|- class=\"hintergrundfarbe9\"\n! rowspan=\"3\" | Party\n! colspan=\"3\" | 2015\n! colspan=\"9\" | 2010\n|- class=\"hintergrundfarbe9\"\n! colspan=\"3\" | St. Veit in der<br />S\u00fcdsteiermark !! colspan=\"3\" | St. Veit<br />am Vogau !! colspan=\"3\" | St. Nikolai<br />ob Dra\u00dfling !! colspan=\"3\" | Weinburg<br />am Sa\u00dfbach\n|- class